description.narrative: Service continuity and data management were affected by COVID-19 and exacerbated by prolonged HW and CHW boycotts. Antenatal care (ANC)-1 dropped to 42%, ANC-4 to 18.8%, 32% of births occurred in health facilities and DPT-3 dipped to 71%. Investments in community sensitization on malaria resulted in 99% of children with suspected malaria being tested and 100% of confirmed cases being treated by CHWs with ACT. UNICEF contributed to the COVID vaccination campaigns that reached 57% of persons over 18 with one dose and 38% to be fully vaccinated. A polio campaign is being planned due four confirmed cases. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/01/2022
